# L9 Global Agent Conventions

## Execution Discipline

- Read every target file completely before modifying.
- Produce complete files — no stubs, no `# TODO`, no placeholder sections.
- When scope exceeds 5 files or touches a protected path, propose a plan and wait for approval before executing.
- Never silently change behavior. State what changes and why.

## Protected Paths — STOP and Ask Before Touching

- `uv.lock` — only modified by `uv lock` or `uv add`
- `pyproject.toml` — run `uv lock` after any change
- `.github/workflows/*.yml`
- `observability/docker-compose.observability.yml`
- `src/l9_service/observability/bootstrap.py`

## Quality Gate — MUST Pass Before Completing Any Task

1. `uv run ruff format --check src/ tests/` — passes
2. `uv run ruff check src/ tests/` — passes
3. `uv run pyright src/` — 0 new errors
4. `uv run pytest tests/ -x --tb=short` — passes

## INVARIANTS — Never Violate

- No `print()` in `src/` — use `get_logger(__name__)`
- No `eval`, `exec`, `compile` anywhere
- `_provider_override` and `Metrics._test_provider` MUST only appear in test fixture code
- `healthz` and `readyz` MUST remain unauthenticated
- `uv.lock` MUST be committed and current
